(375, 'Court of Appeal Case Management System and Web Interface changes', '1. General / Public Web Interface\r\n•	Languages: The interface must support Sinhala, Tamil, and English.\r\n•	Slider Images: Needs to be changed.\r\n•	Judgments & Orders:\r\no	Add a section for \"Latest Judgments/Orders\".\r\no	Add a Dropdown for \"All Judgments and Orders\".\r\no	Judgment archive should cover from 2011 to Now.\r\n•	Notices: Add the Court Calendar to the Notices section.\r\n•	Citizen\'s Charter: This needs to be changed/updated.\r\n•	Documents: Should be the same documents as the Supreme Court (available in Sinhala, English, and Tamil).\r\n•	Search Function: \"Search your Case\" should show the Next Step and the Case Profile.\r\n•	To Be Listed: This feature should function the same as the early Court of Appeal (COA) website.\r\n•	Formatting: Format example noted: CA/APPEAL/203/2025.\r\n________________________________________\r\n2. Dashboard (Admin System)\r\n•	Cards: Change the label \"Total Cases\" to \"Active Cases\" (or Pending Cases).\r\n________________________________________\r\n3. All Cases Page\r\n•	Columns: Change \"Next Step\" to represent Argument / Next Action.\r\n•	Buttons: Change \"Before / Not Before\" to \"Before\" (e.g., indicating the Bench).\r\n________________________________________\r\n4. New Case Registration\r\n•	Petitioner Info: Update the label to include \"Appellant\'s / Petitioner / Complainer\'s Information\".\r\n•	Receipt Number: This field needs to be scannable.\r\n•	Bail Selection: When \"Bail\" is selected, add optional fields for Suspect/Accused Details.\r\n•	Lower Court: Update label to \"Lower Court / Tribunals / Institution\".\r\n•	New Fields & Features:\r\no	Add Stamp Duty charges field.\r\no	Add Print option for the new case.\r\no	Include QR and Barcode print options.\r\n________________________________________\r\n5. Next Action Module\r\n•	Judgment Delivered: When this action is selected, the Judge\'s Name is requested.\r\n•	Special Constituted Bench:\r\no	Allow adding a maximum of 5 Judges\' names.\r\no	Logic: If a 5-Judge Bench is selected, automatically set the Court Room to 301.\r\n•	Connected Cases: Add fields to handle connected cases.', 4, 4, 'completed', 'high', '2025-12-22', '2025-12-14 05:47:57', '2025-12-22 07:47:52'),
