(623, 'Dash lk', 'Dear SLT ,\r\n \r\nThank you for getting back to us. I am Jovita, reaching out to you in response to case #E-492701 submitted regarding the email issue. We appreciate your patience while we took care of this for you.\r\n\r\nI understand how important it is to be able to manage your email accounts reliably so that you can contact customers, and I\'m sorry to know that you have been having difficulties with this.\r\n\r\nFrom the case details, I understand that you are getting bounceback while sending email to Gmail accounts as \"Gmail has detected that this message is likely 550-5.7.1 unsolicited mail. To reduce the amount of spam sent to Gmail, 550-5.7.1 this message has been blocked\"\r\n\r\nI did confirm that the account is not sending a large number of emails. I\r\n\r\nHowever, Google has temporarily put a block on your emails. This is typically reviewed every 3-5 days and should be removed within that time frame. If it continues for longer than that, you can submit a manual request for removal. As for Google, you will want to review this article to confirm your emails are within their sending guidelines and then use the form below for further assistance   https://support.google.com/mail/contact/bulk_send_new.\r\n\r\nGmail blocks emails if you include links to known spam sources or sites in your emails. Affiliate programs and third-party email marketing tools can trigger domain reputation issues. If you have a low domain reputation, Gmail may block both your domain and your IP address. If you are sending large volumes of emails, I recommend you review Gmail’s Sender Guidelines.\r\n\r\nGoing forward, the best way to avoid an email from being compromised is to update the passwords for your email accounts once every 3 months, as well as ensure there is a Google reCAPTCHA on any contact/input form on the sites.\r\n \r\n\r\nA heads-up: To gain better insights into your email performance and reputation, I recommend utilizing the Google Postmaster Tools, a free online resource provided by Google. This tool will help you ana', 9, 9, 'completed', 'high', '2026-03-23', '2026-03-23 06:12:22', '2026-03-23 11:52:33'),
