(927, 'Alucomass (Pvt) Ltd', 'Portfolio Website UI Design', 22, 22, 'completed', 'high', '2026-07-22', '2026-07-22 04:33:27', '2026-07-22 12:59:06'),
(928, 'GEM LMS', 'Changes for  System Administrator  \r\nUser Management \r\n1. The system should keep a complete log history of all actions, such as edit, delete, login date, \r\nand login time. \r\n2. User roles should be arranged and listed in a set order. \r\n3. When a new login is created for a user, the system should not ask the admin to enter a \r\npassword at that point (there is no password field in the prototype). We need to confirm \r\nhow login details will be shared with the user without setting a password here. \r\n4. There are two Diploma courses – Diploma in Gemmology and Diploma in Jewellery. Each \r\ncourse\'s own Course Coordinator should only be able to enter data for their own course. \r\n5. Change the label “Center Administrator” to “Center Administration”. \r\n6. Limit access so that an instructor can only view and manage the course(s) assigned to them. \r\n7. When creating a new user role , there should be an option to upload that user\'s e-signature. \r\nCenter Administration \r\n8. The Center ID format and numbering order will be provided by us. \r\n9. Include Office In-Charge (OIC) details, such as OIC Name and OIC \r\n• Add a table with the following columns, in this order: Batch Code, Student ID, Student Name, \r\nCenter, Completed Course, Completion Date. \r\n• A student can be enrolled in more than one course. When a student is being terminated, if \r\nthat student is following more than one course, the status of their other ongoing course(s) \r\nshould be shown to the System Administrator. \r\nNote: Only students who have fully completed their course should be terminated. Students who \r\nare still in an ongoing batch should remain active.', 9, 9, 'pending', 'high', '2026-07-22', '2026-07-22 04:41:23', '2026-07-22 04:41:23'),
(929, 'Matara PS', 'Add Notice back date', 9, 9, 'completed', 'high', '2026-07-22', '2026-07-22 04:42:00', '2026-07-22 12:44:58'),
(930, 'Fleet hub Amc new design ', 'The new Fleet Hub AMC design presents a clean, modern, and professional visual identity with a refined layout, consistent styling, and a structured interface. The refreshed design enhances the overall look and reflects a contemporary approach to fleet maintenance management.', 14, 14, 'completed', 'medium', '2026-07-22', '2026-07-22 04:53:01', '2026-07-22 12:45:20'),
(931, 'HSCOL site need new page ', 'A newly designed introduction page for the HSCOL website, created to deliver a strong first impression with a modern and engaging visual layout. The page highlights the organization\'s identity, key services, and core values while establishing a clear and professional entry point to the website.', 14, 14, 'completed', 'medium', '2026-07-22', '2026-07-22 05:04:47', '2026-07-22 12:44:52'),
